### 4.5 Navigation Pattern (Tab-Switched)

```js
const LABELS = {
  1: '01 — DISCOVERY',
  2: '02 — FEATURE DETAIL',
  3: '03 — SUCCESS',
  4: '04 — OPS / ADMIN'
};

const ANNO = {
  1: [
    { n: 'INSIGHT 01', t: 'Title Here', b: 'Body explanation.', metric: { v: '+22%', l: 'Conversion Lift' } },
    { n: 'INSIGHT 02', t: 'Title Here', b: 'Body explanation.', metric: { v: '3.1x', l: 'Engagement' } },
    { n: 'PM RATIONALE', t: 'Why This Matters', b: 'Strategic reasoning.' }
  ],
  // ... repeat for screens 2–4
};

function go(n) {
  [1,2,3,4].forEach(i => {
    document.getElementById('s'+i).classList.remove('active');
    document.getElementById('d'+i).classList.remove('active');
    document.getElementById('n'+i).classList.remove('active');
  });
  document.getElementById('s'+n).classList.add('active');
  document.getElementById('d'+n).classList.add('active');
  document.getElementById('n'+n).classList.add('active');
  document.getElementById('screen-label').textContent = LABELS[n];
  renderAnno(n);
}

function renderAnno(n) {
  const cards = ANNO[n];
  document.getElementById('anno-cards').innerHTML = cards.map(c => `
    <div class="anno-card">
      <div class="anno-num">${c.n}</div>
      <div class="anno-title">${c.t}</div>
      <div class="anno-body">${c.b}</div>
      ${c.metric ? `<div class="anno-metric"><span class="anno-metric-val">${c.metric.v}</span><span class="anno-metric-lbl">${c.metric.l}</span></div>` : ''}
    </div>
  `).join('');
}
renderAnno(1); // init
```

### 4.6 Mandatory 4 Screens

| # | Screen | Purpose |
|---|--------|---------|
| 1 | Home / Discovery | Main app surface with the feature surfaced (banner, card, feed) |
| 2 | Feature Detail / Tracker | Core mechanics — progress bars, goals, timers, product detail |
| 3 | Success / Completion | Reward moment — confetti, benefit displayed, next-step CTA |
| 4 | Ops / Admin / Nudge | Backstage — how ops team manages/nudges the user |

### 4.7 Phone Anatomy
- Status bar: time left, signal right
- Screen container: `overflow-y: auto; max-height: 724px; scrollbar-width: none`
- Notch: 118px × 28px, dark, border-radius `0 0 16px 16px`
- Camera circle: `.nc` class
- Sensor dot: `.ndot` class (or `.ndot-n`)
- ⚠️ **NEVER use `.ns` as a classname** — it collides with the notch sensor dot (known bug)

### 4.8 Confetti (Screen 3 Standard)

```js
const c = document.getElementById('conf');
const cols = ['#4ADE80','#F97316','#60A5FA','#FBBF24','#F472B6','#A78BFA','#34D399'];
for(let i=0;i<32;i++){
  const p = document.createElement('div');
  p.className='cp';
  const size = 4+Math.random()*7;
  p.style.cssText=`left:${Math.random()*100}%;top:${Math.random()*120-10}%;width:${size}px;height:${size}px;background:${cols[Math.floor(Math.random()*cols.length)]};border-radius:${Math.random()>.5?'50%':'2px'};animation-duration:${1.4+Math.random()*1.8}s;animation-delay:${Math.random()*2.4}s;`;
  c.appendChild(p);
}
```

### 4.9 Progress Bar Component

```html
<div class="track"><div class="fill" style="width:[N]%"><span class="fill-badge">[N]%</span></div></div>
```
```css
.track { height:8px; background:#e2e8f0; border-radius:99px; overflow:visible; position:relative; }
.fill { height:100%; border-radius:99px; background:var(--c-bright); position:relative; transition:.6s ease; }
.fill-badge { position:absolute; right:-2px; top:-9px; background:var(--c-bright); color:#fff; font-size:9px; font-weight:700; padding:2px 5px; border-radius:6px; }
```

### 4.10 Annotation Panel
- Fixed width: 300px, positioned to the right of the prototype frame
- 3 cards per screen: `INSIGHT 01`, `INSIGHT 02`, `PM RATIONALE` (or `DESIGN DECISION`)
- Each card has: tag label → title → body → optional metric callout
- Metric callout: large value + small label

### 4.11 Prototype QA Checklist

- [ ] All 4 screens render without overlap
- [ ] No class name collisions (especially `.ns`)
- [ ] Scrollable content doesn't overflow the phone chrome
- [ ] Fonts load (Sora + DM Mono)
- [ ] Confetti animates on Screen 3
- [ ] Progress bars show fill-badge correctly
- [ ] Touch targets ≥ 44px
- [ ] Company colors consistent across all 4 screens
- [ ] Annotation panel renders 3 cards per screen

