## 5 · CEO DECK TEMPLATE (Phase 3)

### 5.1 File Convention
- Build script: `assets/build-[company-slug]-[feature]-deck.js`
- Output: `assets/[company-slug]-[feature]-deck.pptx`
- Run: `node assets/build-[company-slug]-[feature]-deck.js`

### 5.2 Best Reference Sample
**`assets/build-adyen-smartcheckout-deck.js`** — cleanest structure, covers all 8 slides with consistent patterns.

### 5.3 Boilerplate

```js
const PptxGenJS = require('pptxgenjs');
const prs = new PptxGenJS();
prs.layout = 'LAYOUT_16x9'; // 10" × 7.5"

const C = {
  dark:   '[HEX_NO_HASH]',   // e.g. '0D1F12'
  hero:   '[SLIGHTLY_LIGHTER]',
  bright: '[ACCENT]',
  orange: '[HIGHLIGHT]',
  white:  'FFFFFF',
  lgray:  'F1F5F9',
  muted:  '94A3B8',
};

// ⚠️ MUST be a factory function — never reuse the same shadow object
const makeShadow = () => ({
  type: 'outer', color: '000000', blur: 3, offset: 1, angle: 45, opacity: 0.12
});
```

### 5.4 Mandatory 8-Slide Structure

| # | Name | Background | Key Elements |
|---|------|-----------|-------------|
| 1 | **Cover** | Dark | Product name (28-30pt), subtitle, "By Ajay Avaghade", company tag, big stat bottom-right |
| 2 | **The Problem** | Dark | "THE PROBLEM" eyebrow (9pt, ALL CAPS), H1 with stat, 3 stat columns, insight box |
| 3 | **The Insight** | Light | "THE INSIGHT" eyebrow, H1, 2-column comparison (❌ current vs ✅ proposed), VS oval |
| 4 | **The Mechanic** | Dark | "THE MECHANIC" eyebrow, H1, 5-step numbered timeline, connecting dashed line |
| 5 | **The Product** | Light | "THE PRODUCT" eyebrow, H1, 2×2 card grid (one per screen) |
| 6 | **Impact & ROI** | Dark | "IMPACT & ROI" eyebrow, 2×4 metric grid |
| 7 | **Proof of Work** | Split | Left (dark): PhonePe proof. Right (light): JD mapping. Quote box. |
| 8 | **Rollout Plan** | Dark | 3 phase cards, "What I Need" ask box, contact footer |

### 5.5 Typography Rules

| Element | Size | Style |
|---------|------|-------|
| Eyebrow (slide title) | 9–10pt | ALL CAPS, 0.08em letterSpacing, muted |
| H1 (main heading) | 26–30pt | Bold, high contrast |
| Body / metric labels | 13–14pt | Regular |
| Big stat numbers | 36–44pt | Bold, accent color |
| Footer / captions | 9–10pt | Muted |

### 5.6 Design Rules

- ❌ NEVER use underline accent lines under titles (AI cliché)
- ✅ Use background color blocks or whitespace to separate
- Every slide must have ≥ 1 visual element (shape, colored block, icon character)
- Alternate dark/light (sandwich): Dark → Dark → Light → Dark → Light → Dark → Light → Dark
- No `#` prefix on hex colors in PptxGenJS
- Apostrophes inside single-quoted JS strings cause `SyntaxError` — always rephrase or escape

### 5.7 Deck QA

```bash
python3 -c "
from pptx import Presentation
prs = Presentation('assets/[company]-[feature]-deck.pptx')
for i, slide in enumerate(prs.slides, 1):
    print(f'--- SLIDE {i} ---')
    for shape in slide.shapes:
        if shape.has_text_frame:
            for para in shape.text_frame.paragraphs:
                t = para.text.strip()
                if t: print(t)
"
```
Check: missing slides, placeholder text (XXX, TODO, lorem), must be exactly 8 slides.

