**Button classes**: ALWAYS use `btn btn-primary rw-btn` and `btn btn-outline rw-btn` — never invent new classes.

### 6.2 Deep Link
URL format: `https://ajay-avaghade.github.io/Portfolio/#real-world/[company-slug]`
Hash router already exists in index.html — just ensure `id="rw-[company-slug]"` is on the block.
⚠️ **WARNING**: When sharing the link with Ajay, ALWAYS provide the `#real-world/` URL. NEVER share the raw DOM ID (`#rw-`).

### 6.3 Git Workflow
```bash
git add index.html [company]-[feature]-prototype.html assets/[company]-[feature]-deck.pptx assets/build-[company]-[feature]-deck.js
git commit -m "Add [Company] [Feature] case study — prototype + CEO deck"
git push origin main
```
⚠️ **FATAL DEPLOYMENT RISK**: NEVER use `git add .`, `git add -A`, or `git commit -a`. This previously committed a massive `venv/` directory which caused GitHub Pages to silently crash and fail to deploy the website. ALWAYS add exactly the 4 files specified above.

