## 7 · RESUME TEMPLATE (Phase 5)

### 7.1 Output Path
`/Users/ajayavaghade/Job Apply AI/Ajay_Avaghade_Resume_[Company].html`

### 7.2 Core Rules

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **Clone, Don't Create** | NEVER write the resume HTML/CSS from scratch. ALWAYS read the most recent successful resume (e.g., `Ajay_Avaghade_Resume_FINN.html`) and duplicate its exact structure, CSS, and contact header. Only modify the Role Title, Professional Summary, and Case Studies sections. |
| **One page** | STRICT. Must fit A4/Letter. Must also be >85% filled. |
| **Font** | Inter, 8.4pt body, never below 8.2pt |
| **Margins** | `@page { margin:.22in .28in; size:letter; }` — proven tight-but-safe |
| **Text justify** | `text-align:justify; text-align-last:left` on ALL text — kills orphan stretching |
| **Title** | Mirrors JD language exactly (e.g., JD says "Senior PM, Growth" → "Product Manager — Growth & Monetization") |
| **STAR bullets** | Every bullet: Situation (15 words) → Action (20 words) → Result (metric, 10 words) |
| **Bold metrics** | Must appear MID-sentence, never trailing |
| **Last line rule** | Every bullet's last line must have ≥ 6 words |
| **Case study separation** | Experience bullets NEVER reference the case study built for this application |
| **Summary ending** | Name + ≤5-word description of case study. No metrics, no mechanics. |

### 7.3 Section Order (Mandatory)

1. **Name** (large, centered, bold)
2. **Role title** (centered, italic, adapted to JD)
3. **Contact line** (city, phone, email, LinkedIn, Portfolio)
4. **Relocation line** (UAE only; custom for other countries; omit for India)
5. **PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY** — 3–4 sentences, opens with category + years, mentions company domain, ends with case study signal
6. **EXPERIENCE** — Reverse chronological, STAR bullets, 2–3 per role
7. **EDUCATION** — IIM, NEOMA, VNIT
8. **SKILLS** — Two rows: "Product & Strategy" and "Data & AI Tools"
9. **CASE STUDIES** — The case study just built. Format: `• [Title] — [1-sentence what was solved]. [prototype] [deck]`
10. **PROJECTS & SIDE BUILDS** — Do NOT include all 3 side projects by default. Depending on the remaining vertical space (to keep the resume strictly to one page and >85% filled), pick 1, 2, or all 3 projects in this sequence: (1) AI Mock PM Interviewer, (2) Job Apply AI, and (3) Antigravity Resume Agent. Make them hyperlinked using HTML anchor tags pointing to their URLs: AI Mock PM Interviewer (https://huggingface.co/spaces/ajay-avaghade/AI-Mock-Product-Manager-Interviewer), Job Apply AI (https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/antigravity-apply/accbghdhdmdigaohfaggdcnjlifdclbc), Antigravity Resume Agent (https://ajay-avaghade.github.io/Antigravity-Resume-Agent/index.html). Additionally, include 1-2 most relevant portfolio case studies (excluding the current company's).
    Format each project as a bullet with an anchor tag:
    - `• <a href="https://huggingface.co/spaces/ajay-avaghade/AI-Mock-Product-Manager-Interviewer" target="_blank">AI Mock PM Interviewer</a> — Conversational AI for structured PM interview practice with real-time coaching feedback.`
    - `• <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/antigravity-apply/accbghdhdmdigaohfaggdcnjlifdclbc" target="_blank">Job Apply AI</a> — Chrome extension auto-filling job applications on LinkedIn, Workday, Lever, Greenhouse; AI-generated outreach emails.`
    - `• <a href="https://ajay-avaghade.github.io/Antigravity-Resume-Agent/index.html" target="_blank">Antigravity Resume Agent</a> — Gemini-powered multi-agent pipeline (6 parallel agents) auto-generating >90 ATS-scored resumes from a JD URL.`
11. **AWARDS & RECOGNITION** — All 3 awards

### 7.4 CSS Baseline (Proven Working)

```css
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap');
* { margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing:border-box; }
body { font-family:'Inter',Arial,sans-serif; font-size:8.4pt; color:#1a1a1a; background:#fff; padding:14px 26px; max-width:800px; margin:0 auto; line-height:1.35; }
.name       { font-size:19pt; font-weight:700; text-align:center; letter-spacing:.04em; }
.role-title { font-size:9pt; font-style:italic; text-align:center; color:#444; margin:1px 0 2px; }
