.edu-name { font-size:8.6pt; font-weight:600; }
.edu-date { font-size:7.6pt; color:#555; }
.edu-sub  { font-size:7.6pt; color:#555; font-style:italic; margin-bottom:2px; }
a { color:#1a56db; font-weight:500; text-decoration:none; }
.awards-line { font-size:8.1pt; line-height:1.42; text-align:justify; text-align-last:left; }
@media print { body { padding:0; } @page { margin:.22in .28in; size:letter; } }
```

### 7.5 Resume QA Checklist

**Page check:**
- [ ] Exactly 1 page in Chrome print preview (⌘P)
- [ ] Page is >85% filled — not ending halfway
- [ ] If overflowing: reduce `@page` margins first, then trim text. Never shrink font below 8.2pt

**Case study separation check:**
- [ ] No experience bullet names or describes the case study built for this application
- [ ] Summary ends with case study name + ≤5-word description only
- [ ] Case studies section = name + 1 sentence + links only

**Orphan line check:**
- [ ] No bullet's last line has fewer than 6 words
- [ ] No bold metric phrase is the trailing text on a bullet
- [ ] Awards paragraph doesn't end with a single standalone word

**Content check:**
- [ ] Role title mirrors JD language
- [ ] Top 7 JD keywords in summary + skills
- [ ] Every bullet is STAR-structured
- [ ] Case study links to prototype + deck
- [ ] Relocation line correct (present/absent based on location)
- [ ] No invented metrics
- [ ] All links work

### 7.6 Generate PDF & After Delivery
Automatically generate the PDF from the HTML using headless Chrome:
```bash
/Applications/Google\ Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google\ Chrome --headless --no-pdf-header-footer --print-to-pdf="/Users/ajayavaghade/Job Apply AI/Ajay_Avaghade_Resume_[Company].pdf" "file:///Users/ajayavaghade/Job Apply AI/Ajay_Avaghade_Resume_[Company].html"
```
Then open both the PDF and HTML:
```bash
open "/Users/ajayavaghade/Job Apply AI/Ajay_Avaghade_Resume_[Company].pdf"
open -a "Google Chrome" "/Users/ajayavaghade/Job Apply AI/Ajay_Avaghade_Resume_[Company].html"
```
Always provide the quick-edit tip:
> **Quick edits:** In Chrome, press ⌘⌥I → Console → type `document.body.contentEditable='true'` → Enter. Click any text and edit. Then ⌘P to save as PDF.

